===========================================================
How to Run the Game Database App
===========================================================

This application allows you to look up video games based on 
what platform they are on (like PC, Nintendo Switch, etc.).

STEP 1: GET THE TOOLS READY
---------------------------
1. Make sure you have Node.js installed on your computer.
2. Open your terminal (Command Prompt on Windows or Terminal on Mac).
3. Type the following command and hit Enter to install the 
   necessary "helper" files:
   
   npm install mysql2 readline-sync

STEP 2: PREPARE THE DATABASE
----------------------------
1. Open MySQL Workbench.
2. Open the file 'Hwk7_dbos_colemant.sql' and click the 
   Lightning Bolt icon to run it. This sets up the search 
   logic for the app.

STEP 3: RUN THE APP
-------------------
1. In your terminal, make sure you are in the same folder 
   as the 'GameApp.js' file.
2. Type this command and hit Enter:

   node GameApp.js

STEP 4: USING THE APP
---------------------
1. When asked, type your MySQL Username (usually 'root') 
   and your Password.
2. Choose '1' from the menu to see the list of platforms.
3. Type a platform name from the list (it doesn't matter if 
   you use capital letters or lowercase).
4. The app will show you the games!
5. When you are finished, choose '2' to exit.

-----------------------------------------------------------
Language used for this project: JavaScript (Node.js)
===========================================================